'''WinImage''' is a disk imaging [[Application software|application]] for [[Microsoft Windows]] created by Gilles Vollant Software. Its features include creating, reading and editing [[disk image]]s and also opening [[VMware]] and [[Microsoft Virtual PC]] hard disk images. WinImage is able to mount an ISO image using the freeware FileDisk driver.
Even though it has been a 32-bit program from its beginnings, it utilized the [[Win32s]] system API, so it could run on Windows 3.x. The last version of WinImage to run on Windows 3.x is version 6.1.
Some versions of WinImage bundle [[FileDisk]][http://www.winimage.com/filedisk.htm], a [[Virtual drive|disk emulator]]. ==Format support== WinImage supports the following [[disk image]] formats and [[file system]]s: {| ! File formats ! File systems |- | style = "vertical-align:top;" | * [[Distribution Media Format]] (DMF) * [[VHD (file format)|Virtual Hard Disk]] (VHD) * [[ISO image]] (No [[Universal Disk Format|UDF]] support as of version 8.10) * [[IMA (file format)|IMA and IMZ]] * [[Cue sheet (computing)|Cue sheet]] (CUE) | style = "vertical-align:top;" | * [[File Allocation Table|FAT]] * [[FAT32]] * [[NTFS]] * [[ext2]] |}
